%N A360362 Maximum number of moves required to reach an already visited color configuration, when applying the move described in A360360 to a deck of n colored cards.
%F A360362 a(n) = A357619(n) for 1 <= n <= 8, but it seems unlikely that this holds for all n.
%F A360362 a(n) <= A360360(n) + A360361(n). Equality holds (i.e., the maximum period and the maximum preperiod can be obtained with the same initial configuration) for n = 1, 2, 3, 4, 10, 12, 14, ... .
%e A360362 For n = 5, the initial configuration 01102 (with the top of the deck to the left) requires 9 moves to reach an already visited configuration: 01102 -> 11020 -> 10120 -> 01210 -> 12100 -> 21010 -> 12010 -> 20101 -> 02101 -> 21010. This is the maximum for 5 cards, so a(5) = 9.
